    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <head>139. Message From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d139fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 110.11–DU/12–1755. Secret. Transmitted in <gloss target="#t_Dulte1"
                            >Dulte</gloss> 5 from Paris, 5 p.m., and marked “eyes only Acting
                        Secretary for President from Secretary.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-12-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1955</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. President</hi>: My talks here Saturday with
                        <persName corresp="#p_BH1">von Brentano</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_SPH1">Spaak</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MJ1"
                        >Monnet</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d139fn2">The conversations with <persName corresp="#p_BH1"
                            >von Brentano</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SPH1"
                            >Spaak</persName> are summarized in <gloss target="#t_Secto1"
                            >Secto</gloss> 19, <ref target="#d140">
                            <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                        </ref>, and <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 22, <ref target="#d141"
                            >Document 141</ref>; a memorandum of the conversation with <persName
                            corresp="#p_MJ1">Monnet</persName> is printed <ref target="#d140">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> all show that the British are working hard to block the
                    development of the European idea in terms of atomic energy and a common market.
                    This is somewhat in the same pattern as their early opposition to <gloss
                        target="#t_EDC1">EDC</gloss>. I feel that this is a matter which we will
                    have to discuss seriously with <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName> when they come to
                    Washington.</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Foster</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
